</head>

<body>

<div class="container">


    <h2 class="form-signin-heading">Use this UUID for using Stoot in your application</h2>

    <div class="well">
        <%= uuid %>
    </div>
    <ul>
        <li>Add this code at the bottom of your page: <br>
            <code>
                &lt;script type='text/javascript' src='http://stoot.herokuapp.com/js/stoot.ejs'&gt;
            </code>
        </li>
        <li>Register your API key by calling the following code:
            <code>
                var stoot = new Stoot("<%= uuid.replace('-','') %>");
            </code>
        </li>
        <li>Register a new channel by calling the subscribe method:
            <code>
                var channel = stoot.subscribe("my-channel");
            </code>
        </li>
        <li>Register a new event by calling the bindEvent method:
            <br>
            <code>
                channel.bind("my-event", function(data) {
                console.log(data);
                });

            </code>
        </li>
        <li>Trigger the event by calling the trigger event method:
            <code>
                stoot.trigger("my-channel", "my-event", {msg: "hello"});
            </code>
        </li>
        <li>Or trigger the event by using a utility like curl to do something like :
            <code>
                curl 'http://stoot.herokuapp.com/stoot/triggerEvent' --data='channel=&lt;channel name&gt;&amp;event=&lt;event&gt;&amp;data=&lt;json
                data&gt;&amp;apiKey=&lt;api_key&gt;'
            </code>
            <br>
            ... or a GET call would also do ;)

        </li>
    </ul>


</div>
<!-- /container -->

